                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>HttpClient.execute should throw only one exception, for easier general use.&lt;br/&gt;
HttpMethod constructors (HttpGet, HttpPut, etc..) should throw IllegalArgumentException in the string constructor (imply the string is pre-checked).  People wanting to see a URIException can use &amp;#39;new HttpGet(new URI(uri))&amp;#39; and trigger the exception from the explicit URI creation.</description>
